<rate>5< /rate><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOGON8XTPbZ6LLY4L_U_jEoetHfpTVpS69CuqA=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNy83InCWQCRxXVAnflzRBXvNK1cxvUD9UrSBM=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pictures><name>Patcharee Boyd</name><text>The absolutely best dog park as far as landscaping goes is located in Vallejo!
Better than any other dog parks within an hour or twos drive.
Wardlaw is just a gorgeous park. I almost always end up chit chatting or in conversation with other friendly dog owners. It's not snooty as far as I can tell, people often clean more than their share, no one has gotten upset at barking dog's.
It's a very nice place to spend a few minutes or a few hours with your four legged bark buddies.
Bring your own sanitizer spray. Bags are biodegradable but dificult to open, one kind lady taught me to rip open a small tear at the top to find/create a separation point.
Lots of regulars seem well aquatinted with each other and even if they don't know the humans names, they'll know each other's dogs names.
It's ideal for me as I cannot walk them due to physical limitations.
I can make it walking from one chair location to another and thereby get in a little extra exercise myself. If you don't have painful limitations that doesn't seem like a big deal but it is a great set up for me and a perfect match for my needs. I'll get some better photos, these are only by the very front in the small side. It isn't an accurate representation on how nice it is.<//text>< GmapID>

<Time>1556259977862<//Time>< Rate>
5</Rate>
<Text>I have been to a LOT of dog parks, and this is one of the nicest I've seen. I stop whenever I'm in the area, and it's always in excellent condition. The surface is grass. The large dog park is built on a gentle slope, which I think helps it drain so the turf doesn't get muddy and torn up from rain. (And then patchy and dusty in summer.) The slope and irregular shape make it more interesting than the typical flat rectangle, and there's a path around the perimeter. The people and dogs I've met have all been friendly. Plenty of parking, double gate, small & large dog sections, water, poop bags, and good fencing. Just a pleasant place for your dog and you.< /Text>< pictures>

< text>
The service and good were awesome.   It looks like a pretty small place from the outside, but they have a lot of seating, even on the patio.   They have a great selection of Mexican and American food.    The food was delivered to our table quickly and had a fresh flavor to it and a good serving size.    This is my new favorite Mexican restaurant in town.   Great beer selection also.   Beer is only in bottles. But reasonable prices.< /text>

<rate>4<//rate>< Text>
The food and service were great.  We had a little bit of everything.  The portions were big and filling.  Tortillas are freshly handmade and delicious. Refried beans were seasoned almost like charros.  They start you off with chips and salsa.  You can order appetizers ranging from hot wings and supreme nachos, to queso fundido.  Good selection of sea food.  You can get plate combos or a la carte items like tacos.  The tacos are pretty big too.  Cleanliness was good, plenty of seating, four TV's playing sports.  Family friendly, they provide a kids menu.  Great flavors, I'm coming back.<//Text>

<pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN3JjChUqLaQlB1YfWwsHxMl_OAf8ByTZc_sVJn=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pics><Rating>5<//Rating><resp>None< /resp>< date>

<user_id>117408545090193912413<//user_id><name>Adriana G</name><date>1516326258635< /date><rate>4<//rate>< Text>
Place was nice and clean, attentive personnel that took our order, Cynthia. Food was pleasing to the eye, and pleasing to the palate. I had the carne asada torta, does not come with any hot sauce, you need to ask for some to give it some spice. I asked for the green hot sauce which was tasty. My daughter had a grilled chicken sandwich and she enjoyed it. My husband went for the wet burrito, which tasted ok, but the red sauce used to "wet" the burrito was a bit on the strong side. Not hot spicy, but just a bit too much.  I feel that the deeper the color the more heavy on the taste. It kind of gave it a taste that it came from a powder chili...not necessarily fresh chiles.  My husband stated that the beans might have been from a can, but he might be wrong.  Don't get me wrong, it was ok, but probably will not be ordering the wet burrito in the future if we return.
Prices were average for the food compared to Mexican restaurants. Fountain drinks we're a bit on the flat side.
Other than that place was ok for our first time trying it out.< /Text>

<Text>DO NOT DEAL WITH ANGELICA NAVARRO.

My 1 year lease there was great all the way up until the move out process. It's hard to speak about anything positive about this place when you are left with a bad taste in your mouth upon leaving.

My lease was up on 3/13/2020. On 1/22/2020, I signed their agreement to continue month to month as I was in the process of purchasing a home. The Avella team mentioned that in order to NOT incur any costs, that I'd have to provide a 30 day notice. I formally emailed Avella on 2/13/20 letting them know that I will be moving out on 3/14/20 (which was a complete 30 day notice given that February had 29 days). Angelica emailed me back inquiring whether I wanted to move out on 3/13/20 which is my "original/initial" lease end date. This was the start of COVID-19. Due to high stress from the uncertainty of this pandemic, I didn't pay attention to whether she was trying to manipulate me into a rent responsible charge.

Upon receiving my move out statement, I noticed I was charged 1 day rent responsible which almost amounted to $100. I was shocked and appalled! Never had the leasing team mentioned that I would incur these costs and based on the 30 day notice contract, that option was not selected. I attempted to come to agreement with Angelica when this was realized and she was completely unpleasant and unsympathetic stating that the leasing team does not have time to notify people of this charge. How is that even possible? Every time I go into the leasing office, I see each member of their team on Google Hangouts. If they have time to chat amongst one another, they should have time to ensure their tenants know the costs that will be incurred. Not to mention that their move-out inspection WAS A JOKE. I scheduled my move-out inspection immediately when I received their notice to schedule and they had to reschedule on me. I had to take time out of my work schedule to make sure I was home for the move out inspection. Once the move out inspection was completed, I was told I would be sent the inspection document when the person gets to a place with wifi. THIS NEVER HAPPENED. I actually had to email the leasing office to get a copy of this. Imagine how shady this place feels?!

I would never recommend Avella to anyone. In fact, I've recommended them to Cadenza or Amalfi as they seem to care more about their tenants. For those interested, my lease at #1817 was $2,150 for a 1 bedroom apartment. At my lease renewal, they increased it by 6% or to $2,280 (12 month) or $2,360 (16 months). That's a huge increase for just 1 year. Their community is not worth that sort of increase when their amenities are just OK, when they don't keep up with landscaping, when they do not acknowledge you when you tell them that specific tenants do not pick up their dogs sh*t, or when there's a ton of construction being built for low income families causing noise during times that they are not allowed to do construction.

Save your money and go down the street to Cadenza. I heard that Sandra is now a manager over there and she was a pleasure to work with while she was at Avella. If you're a person that loves amenities and to want a bang for your buck, I'd check out Amalfi in Tustin.< /Text>< Rate>

<Review>I‚Äôll start off this review saying that, until recently, living at Avella has been a fantastic experience.  It‚Äôs quiet, clean, well kept, has fantastic amenities, maintenance requests are taken care of in a timely manner - everything you could ask for in an apartment community/home.  However, the reason for my less than favorable review is because our lease is being terminated due to our building being re-designated as ‚Äúnot pet friendly.‚Äù

All of this would be understandable if Irvine Company/Avella would be more accommodating due to the nature of the request.  The only thing the Irvine Company will help us with is by waiving the ‚Äútransfer fee‚Äù for moving to either a new unit or a new community.   There are currently no other open apartments that are of the same floor plan as the one that we are on.  We also love our location and there doesn‚Äôt appear as if there‚Äôs another unit on site that is comparable.

<Response>None<//Response><Name>Todd Stein</Name>< Review>
We just moved out of Avella and how glad we are in having done so.  I will say first and foremost that maintenance at Avella is great.  No complaint as they do a great job.  Perhaps "management" should take a cue from the maintenance team.  After move out, we got a bill for 500+ dollars for replacing the cheap plastic flooring they put in this place.  There were about 12 pieces that were defective and curling up.  They pinned it on us and said that 54 pieces had to be replaced and charged us for it.  We asked for proof but they never sent any pictures documenting this ruse.  What a joke!!

As this is a non smoking community, I complained several times about neighbors who are habitual smokers who disregard the non smoking aspect of living at Avella and each time they got a slap on the wrist...."Don't do it again!".  If you are seeking a non smoking community, don't move here!!!  More people smoke here than at the no preference communities.  It is absurd that non smoking is not enforced here but it seems like the rule here is that as long as Avella is getting paid they don't want to rock the boat, but if you owe one dollar or management wants what it wants then you are bullied into immediate action.  We originally signed here because they said and promoted (during initial leasing) that they were going to have a dog park.  I spoke with several other (NOW PAST) residents who said they signed because of this too, yet no dog park ever showed up.  I was told by Cassie about 6 months ago that indeed the dog park was in the works and that was a big lie!  I will tell you right now to get everything in writing from the Irvine company as they are liars.  I have been lied to by the management of two communities now.

We did enjoy our apartment aside from the (undocumented, no photo proof given to us) plastic flooring charge that they stuck us with to cover for the poor quality workmanship on this apartments.  Some neighbors we got to know told me they peeked into their unit before it was finished and saw a tequila bottle on the counter.  Nothing says quality work like drunk construction workers.  All in all, I would take a pass on this place!!  Although it is a shame that some people don't feel the need to pick up after their pet, apparently management didn't see fit to have someone keep the community clean either.  Completely unsanitary!!  And many residents just left trash by the trash can instead of putting it in the receptacle. I will add, three kids are frequently unsupervised in the pool areas, screaming and carrying on and nothing done despite this being a liability for Avella.  These same boys getting free hot chocolate and spilling in on the sidewalks and staircases, and being generally dirty and unruly. Yet no action taken whatsoever!

The only good thing I can saw about Avella and its management team at this point is that I don't have to see or deal with the problems of this place having left it. Having spoke to about 10 residents who got nominal rent increases at lease renewal time, the Irvine company definitely targets some they want out with complete and utter inequality of rent increase price gouging.  No matter, we weren't interested in staying anyways and seeing how many people are leaving here this like the place is emptying out so people aren't taking the bait.  I guess this will give management more time to do nothing in running this place properly.  Good luck and good riddance!!

P.S.  ANTS EVERYWHERE!!!<//Review>

< Review>
What an incredible experience renting a U-Haul trailer! From start to finish I was very impressed with the level of communication and service provided by Sam and his staff at this U-Haul location. Had called the shop two weeks before our move to get everything arranged - Sam was very friendly on the phone. He helped coordinate the proper size trailer for our move, and quoted a very reasonable rate. I had called over with a few questions prior to the move, and each time was greeted with a very warm reception and clear information. This is where it gets even better! Come pick-up day I meet Sam in person, and he greets me as if I was family. We get the trailer hooked up, and find that the turn signal fuse was blown on my truck. Sam said no worries, went into the office, found a 10 amp in his stash and helped me get on the road safely. Would absolutely recommend this U-Haul location.</Review>

Got there about 6 pm on a Saturday and it was busy, when I left at 7 pm people were starting to line up at the door.

There are 3 sauces, the regular, 911 and 5150. The 911 sauce is really good, hot enough for people who like spicy food without being too hot so you can't enjoy the food. I got crab, shrimp, corn and sausage. Yes the shrimp is whole shrimp so if you don't like that be aware.

They also have appetizers, we got the super carne asada fries and they are really good. My only real complaint is the crab they use doesn't have much meat in it and it's stringy. It's $17.99 per pound and I feel like I paid for crab shells. I'll go back again for sure, they have a really good menu but the crab just threw me off.</text></record>

< Rating>
2<//Rating>
<Review>If you're going for the Crack N Peal Shrimp that's served by the pound, I would say pass this place up.  I've eaten at several places that are similar to this, The Boiling Crab and the Firehouse Crawfish Cajun Seafood Restaurant both of which are located in Sacramento off Stockton Blvd.  Unfortunately my first visit to Shrimpy's will be my last.  I really enjoy Seafood and was looking forward to having a local place close by that serves up large quantities of great Seafood.  I hate to say it but this isn't the place... and the one in Modesto off of McHenry is equally 2 stars at best.
So far The Firehouse Crawfish Cajun Seafood Restaurant in Sacramento off the 65th expressway and Stockton Blvd is the true King of Crab and Shrimp, The Boiling Crab is a close second.  I really hate to give a bad review especially to a local business.  Unfortunately when you name the business "Shrimpy's" their highlight needs to be Shrimp!!! But that's not the case.  The servers were polite and very helpful, the atmosphere was family style, like sitting at a picnic table loaded with Seafood.  The food quality was just subpar.  To be fair, they did have other things on the menu and from what I saw parked on my neighbors tables it looked pretty good.  For myself, I have to say, take a drive to Sacramento and you'll see the difference between the two places immediately.</Review><pics>None<//pics>< response>
None<//response>

<Rating>5<//Rating><userid>100485784749910669200<//userid>< text>
I never write reviews but I just eat a pumpkin empanada from here and my mind was blown. Let me tell you about it. It was Halloween 2016, my wife And I had just had a baby 3 weeks ago and have been trapped in the house due to this little love bug. We where in the market for a baby Bjorn and found a used one off Craigslist in the magnolia park area. So we packed up the baby and dog and drove the vehicle over that way. The sun was setting a beautiful reddish orange and we didn't have trouble finding the person's house. The house was cute, looked like a 3 bedroom. The family where all outside enjoying the cool Halloween night. The Baby Bjorn was just as advertised so we got it and where like what do we do next? I said I was hungry and looked around on Google maps for a quick bite. Our new baby was half asleep in the back seat so I knew we had some time to find a place. That's when I found World Empanadas! It was less then a mile away so we strolled on over baby and dog in tow and that's when we tried the aforementioned pumpkin empanada. You should DEFINITELY try it... but I'm remembering now that it was a special that day so they probably won't have it when you go. Try something else it's all good!</text>

< rate>
4</rate>
<Resp>None<//Resp>< Text>
A little quaint place that offers quality and clean food that's not greasy .

Pros:  Empanadas are delicious.   They are baked not fried.  Variety of flavors and stuffings are offered.   They also serve soups and salads.

Cons:  I have ordered coffee from them 3 times.  Every single time,  they were lukewarm and NEVER HOT.  I told them about my coffee not being hot.  They reheated my coffee in the microwave!  Each time instead of brewing a fresh batch!  Unreal! I wish I were joking, my wife was with me.  That alone drops a star for me.   I SHOULD HAVE GIVEN THEM 3 STARS just for that.

I also wish for the friendlier staff.  Normally the ones at the register taking order are the friendliest ones.  But the ones serving the food not so much.  When I pay $3.40 for each empanada,  I expect a great service.

Just today alone, my bill was over $100.00.  I am sure the mgmt is listening.< /Text>

< Review>
Okay - not totally sure they deserve 5 stars but it was good for what it was. The service was certainly fine. You have to remember this is closer to a fast food place than a 5 star so, service was okay. The food was okay - again - for it being this type of place. The problem I had is that most of my hispanic friends would have never made Empanadas like this. Everything appeared baked and our meal was served not hot so the whole Mexican Empanadas thing kinda got lost. If you like Empanadas and you are expecting authentic then this is not your place. On the other hand if you want decent food at a decent price then this just might be for you.<//Review>

They have about 18 selections, which ranges from meat fillings to dessert fillings. I was able to try 3 of them, including the chile con carne, Sante Fe Chicken, and banana nutella. I liked them all. The chile con carne and sante fe chicken had a nice taste to it, and kind of spicy as well. The crust texture is pretty awesome. I was also surprised at how well empanadas tasted as desserts, especially with the delicious nutella filling. What's cool is that you can eat the empanadas in store, and take out as well.

I would recommend this place. The selections are nice, the taste is great, and the prices are reasonable. It's the only store of its kind in Burbank, which alone makes this a local business to support in the area. I have a video of my food adventures here on my YouTube channel called Rockstar Eater if you are interested in seeing it.<//Text>< pictures>

<Text>I‚Äôve been searching for my dog, and a lead led me here... I originally came to just sus it out. < username>
Cassandra Yeh<//username>
<Response>None</Response>< text>
The Service: Order at the counter. They do have indoor/outdoor seating. It is very nice to meet with one of the owners, Chris. He personally took my order. When I told him it is my first time here, he took time to explain about their store, the concept and most important he gave me great recommendation of what to try. Excellent customer service!!

They also do local delivery & catering. You can even call & order ahead. Save time!!

The Food: I ordered 4 different kind of empanadas....

Santa Fe Chicken - Chicke breast simmered with black beans, corn, bell peppers, onions and tomatoes with spicy cayenne seasoning.

Potato & Cheese - Freshly diced potato sauteed with herbs and spices, simmered in a green jalapeno sauce with mozzarella cheese. Because of the green jalapeno sauce, just a little bit of heat. I like it~

Mixed Berries - Strawberries, blueberries, raspberries, and blackberries with brown sugar (vegan). I love my dessert a little bit sour. I definitely don't feel guilty when I eat this dessert... super refreshing!

Nutella & Banana - Well.... I don't think I need to put description for this yummy dessert, right? Everything with Nutella tastes GOOOOD!!!

LOVE LOVE LOVE the different dipping sauces that they offer. You can definitely eat it without the sauce because the filling inside the empanadas are very flavorful already.

The Parking: Small private lot next to the store and street parking (free).<//text>

< Text>
The empanadas were lovely, I really liked the creamy corn one.  Also, having empanadas sparked an interesting conversation with me and my friends about what the equivalent of an empanada is for various cuisines.  For polish people, it's the perogi.  For Italians, it's the calzone.  For Americans, it's the hot pocket.  Interesting stuff.</Text>

< Text>
The empanadas are delicious, the chimichurri sauce was excellent.... but I don't think they went together too well. Instead of using the sauce as a dip I used the sauce to cook with the next day (they gave us a decent amount of it). They have many vegan and vegetarian options, but the potatoes and cheese was SUPER spicy! I still loved it, but it would have been nice to have a warning. I will definitely be back for the empanadas and chimichurri sauce.</Text>
